t","content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"enumerate","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"introspection"},{"type":"text","text":" functions in "},{"code":"vtable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" are used to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"convey, to remote callers, what nodes exist in the subtree rooted"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"objectPath"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When handling remote calls into any node in the subtree, first the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"enumerate"},{"type":"text","text":" function is used to check if the node exists. If the node exists"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"or the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dispatchToUnenumeratedNodes"},{"text":" flag is set","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"introspection"},{"type":"text","text":" function is used to check if the node supports the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"requested method. If so, the "},{"code":"dispatch","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" function is used to determine"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"where to dispatch the call. The collected ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusInterfaceVTable"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"gpointer","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be used to call into the interface vtable for processing","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the request."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"All calls into user-provided code will be invoked in the thread-default","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"main context (see [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default"},{"text":"])","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of the thread you are calling this method from."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If an existing subtree is already registered at "},{"code":"objectPath","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"then "},{"code":"error","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is set to ","type":"text"},{"code":"exists","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that it is valid to register regular objects (using","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_dbus_connection_register_object()"},{"text":") in a subtree registered with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_dbus_connection_register_subtree()"},{"text":" - if so, the subtree handler","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is tried as the last resort. One way to think about a subtree","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"handler is to consider it a fallback handler for object paths not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"registered via "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_dbus_connection_register_object()"},{"type":"text","text":" or other bindings."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"vtable"},{"text":" will be copied so you cannot change it after","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"registration."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"See this ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"#class@Gio.DBusConnection#an-example-for-exporting-a-subtree"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for an example of how to use this meth